hotspot.title: Our Early Childhood Centre
hotspot.description: Our long day childcare centre and preschool offers care and education for children aged 6 months - 5+ years. Located as part of our Findon campus, the Early Childcare Centre is inspired by the Reggio Emilia approach to the Early Years Curriculum.

hotspot.title: Providing Excellence in Care and Education
hotspot.description: Our Early Childhood Centre was recently assessed and rated by the Education Standards Board, achieving the rating of ‘exceeding’ in all seven Quality Areas and Standards. Due to the outstanding result, the service is now eligible to apply for the Excellent rating; the highest rating an education and care service can achieve under the National Quality Framework. In additon to this, our centre has been awarded and recognised as an ‘Inclusion Aware’ service by Gowrie South Australia for the commitment to identifying any barriers to inclusion

hotspot.title: A Catholic Community of Welcome
hotspot.description: Nazareth Catholic Community is a place of welcome, connecting faith, family and education. Inspired by Jesus of Nazareth and our patrons we are people of justice each committed to building community, nourishing family life and making the world a better place

hotspot.title: Safety of our Young People
hotspot.description: The safety of our young people is paramount, and entry to the Centre is by security coding.

hotspot.title: Our Centre’s Operations
hotspot.description: Our Centre is open for 48 weeks per year from 7am - 6pm from Monday to Friday for education and care. Children can come for all or part of the day, covered by one daily fee. Preschool/ Kindy Our Preschool operates during the school terms from 8:15am - 3:45pm. Childcare is available outside of school terms. Children are eligible for 15 hours (2 days) Preschool per week during school terms.

hotspot.title: For more about our Centre Operations
Your Child’s Weekly Learning Plans
hotspot.description: Your child’s weekly learning plans are displayed, providing the opportunity for discussion and engagement between families, children and our staff.

hotspot.title: Supporting Drop Off and Collection
hotspot.description: Your child is supported by our educators at drop off and collection times. An electronic sign In and out system is used daily and an optional door bell for each room is available for families to enable independence.

hotspot.title: Our Catholic Identity
hotspot.description: Our Catholic identity is expressed and highlighted in many ways and integrated in many activities within the centre, and a Prayer Space is located in each room.

hotspot.title: McAuley/ Catherine Neighbourhood
hotspot.description: The spacious McAuley / Catherine rooms operate as one community, hosting a variety of learning areas including a quiet space, dramatic play, creative thinking, investigations, construction and emergent literacy and numeracy experiences

hotspot.title: Play-Based Learning
hotspot.description: Our rooms provide stimulating play-based learning opportunities which awaken children’s senses and provide opportunities for speculating, explaining, engaging in sustained thinking and problem solving.

hotspot.title: Your Child’s Sleep and Relaxation
hotspot.description: Your child’s sleep and rest routines are important and our learning environments transition into a place of ambient sleep and relaxation, where stretcher beds, quiet activities and soothing music is provided.

hotspot.title: Dedicated Change Areas

hotspot.title: Sharing Meals Together

hotspot.title: Supporting Individual Learning Needs
hotspot.description: Each of the different classroom Neighbourhood spaces is designed to allow flexible learning environments for our students. Furniture that allows for students to collaborate and work together is an essential part of our learning spaces. A variety of different furniture and learning areas allow students to move around throughout their school day to a space that best supports their individual learning needs.

hotspot.title: Alternative Learning Environments
hotspot.description: Each neighbourhoods’ breakout space can create alternative learning environments.

hotspot.title: Mid-Year Reception Intake
hotspot.description: We offer a mid-year Reception intake for families, with a comprehensive transition program “Loving, Learning, Thriving”

hotspot.title: Engaging in the Arts
hotspot.description: Our McAuley Gallery is home to a designated Visual Arts space for all art activities including drawing, painting, printmaking and clay work. We have a specialised art teacher and all year levels engage in Art across the year.

hotspot.title: Group Work
hotspot.description: Stools and large tables allow for group work and room for large artworks.

hotspot.title: Community Projects
hotspot.description: Our community members, including parents, wise owls and parishioners have worked together over a number of years to create a community mosaic project utilising the McAuley Gallery.

hotspot.title: Sharing Spaces
hotspot.description: The Jubilee Rooms is a shared space for Expressive Arts and Out of School Hours Care and the Vacation Care Program. Dance and Drama are specialist subjects taught to all year levels in this space across the year.

hotspot.title: A Place for Creativity and Imagination
hotspot.description: The Jubilee room is a space where classes come together to create the magic of performing art using their creativity and imagination. It is a space where we have rehearsals for various school events and concerts including large productions such as Musicals, Wakakirri and Christmas Concert.

hotspot.title: Technology to Support Unique Learning Styles
hotspot.description: We use various technology such as iPads, cameras, interactive whiteboards, and Bluetooth devices to develop students’ lifelong learning, giving them opportunities to use Green Screen for iMovies and filming, as well as various apps to create unique ways to present their work.

hotspot.title: Clevertouch Screen
hotspot.description: Use of Clever Touch screens to engage learners in interactive resources

hotspot.title: Building Independence and Collaboration
hotspot.description: Students are immersed in whole class guided tasks, Neighbourhood activities, rotation based lessons as well as independent work tasks throughout their school day. Each of these learning styles allows for students to build skills in independence, collaboration and team work at Nazareth.

hotspot.title: Designated Playgrounds
hotspot.description: Junior primary students can play on a designated playground in this area. The playground is also used by our early years children from the Early Childhood Centre and OSHC after school.

hotspot.title: Call to Care for God’s Creation
hotspot.description: Our resident chickens are cared for by our team of student Eco Chiefs, fostering a love of nature and call to care for God’s creation.

hotspot.title: Dramatic Play
hotspot.description: The stage and open structure nurtures creative and dramatic play for our younger students.

hotspot.title: Inquiry Based Learning Opportunities
hotspot.description: Students have the opportunity for hands on experiments and inquiry based learning in our Discovery Centre. The Discovery Centre is a specialist facility for science, with a dedicated Education Support Officer who assists in lessons.

hotspot.title: Abundance of Resources
hotspot.description: An abundance of resources enable students to collaborate or work individually in activities.

hotspot.title: Dedicated Spaces for Exploration
hotspot.description: Our students have dedicated spaces for their work to be displayed. Regularly throughout the year, displays are created from items children bring from their homes or travels. Habitats of animals on loan from the Nature Education Centre feature within the centre allowing students to explore further.

hotspot.title: Building A Love of Literacy
hotspot.description: Our Resource Centre is a hub for building a love of literacy. Take home readers, a lexile book collection and a large variety of both fiction and non fiction books helps to develop each child’s comprehension skills as well as researching and reading for enjoyment.

hotspot.title: More than Books
hotspot.description: The Resource Centre is hive of activity throughout the day, including before and after school, where students can engage in board games, puzzles, lego and colouring in.

hotspot.title: Spaces to Engage and Collaborate
hotspot.description: Providing a large space for multiple classes to engage and collaborate, the Resource Centre is equipped with an interactive screen and various spaces for neighbourhoods and the Early Childhood Centre to utilise as flexible learning spaces.

hotspot.title: Mercy Music Suite
hotspot.description: The Mercy Music Suite is our specialist space for music across all year levels. The suite includes choir and band rehearsal rooms as well as individual tuition rooms. A wide array of cocurricular ensembles are available for students to participate in including concert and rock bands, junior primary and Catholic Schools Music Festival Choir.

hotspot.title: Private Instrumental Tuition
hotspot.description: Instrumental tuition is available for voice, violin, piano, percussion/drums, guitar, flute, clarinet, saxophone, trumpet, trombone & French horn

hotspot.title: Year 5 Curriculum Experience
hotspot.description: In Year 5, students learn either a woodwind or brass instrument as part of their curriculum for the entire year. As part of their experience, students have the opportunity to participate in a Year 5 band and perform at various concerts. Many students then continue with private tuition and progress into the College bands. The cost of the Year 5 Instrumental program is included in annual tuition fees.

hotspot.title: Breakout Spaces
hotspot.description: Our Breakout spaces promote collaboration and flexible learning for students. Students can work in the breakout spaces in groups or pairs or alternatively, students can retreat to work independently outside their classroom in this open space.

hotspot.title: Five Habits of Excellence
hotspot.description: Nazareth aspires to excellence in learning and success for all. We partner with families in a shared responsibility between home and school to support all learners. The five habits are: Attendance, Punctuality, Application, Completion of Work and Involvement.

hotspot.title: Nazareth Capabilities - Skills for Success
hotspot.description: At Nazareth students are explicitly taught and supported in their development of key capabilities. We believe these capabilities foster personal development for our learners in the areas of - Identity- Managing Self- Thinking & Questioning- Collaboration and Connecting & Reflecting.

hotspot.title: Student Responsibility
hotspot.description: Nazareth’s Purpose Statement guides us as followers of Jesus as we are called to love one another. At Nazareth it is our call to support students, together with families, in their social and emotional development, and we aspire to teach our students how to interact with others in a meaningful and loving way, how to resolve conflict with one another and how to understand their own emotions and feelings as they grow and develop in our care.

hotspot.title: Engaging in Independent Online Learning
hotspot.description: From Year 5 onwards, students receive a school owned laptop for their learning. Families are involved in our annual Cyber Safety Evening which aims to teach both student and parents about responsibilities, risks and rewards of having their own device. Students begin to engage in online learning through our school platform SEQTA, receiving assignments and due dates electronically, submitting work online and learning important ICT skills that will support them in their ongoing lifelong learning journey.

hotspot.title: Student Leadership
hotspot.description: As leaders of our Primary years (R-6) at Nazareth, our Year 6 students have the opportunity to apply for various leadership roles, including a Captain position. Primary Captains are selected for each House group as well as each specialist area. These captains hold a special responsibility as role models to their fellow peers, acting as representatives of our community. Various other student leadership opportunities are provided on a semester basis for other year levels including Student Leaders and Eco-Chiefs.

hotspot.title: Building Resilience
hotspot.description: Students across all year levels are immersed in conversations in their learning at Nazareth around Positive Psychology. From Reception to Year 6, teachers provide opportunities for students to explore having a ‘Growth mindset’ and use the analogy of ‘The Learning Pit’ to support them in verbalising their understanding of how they learn and persevere through challenges. These opportunities allow students to build resilience, empower them to use positive self-talk and create a safe environment that welcomes and embraces mistakes as part of the learning process.

hotspot.title: Preparing for Secondary Schooling
hotspot.description: Students begin the transition to secondary school at our Flinders Park campus early in Semester Two each year. These transitions involve visits to our Flinders Park campus as well as involvement in a key days such as Naz Day and the Mental Health & Wellbeing Day, focusing specifically on topics that are relevant and topical to them as they begin this move into a secondary school setting.

hotspot.title: Cafe
hotspot.description: Our community can come to enjoy the hospitality and service of the Nazareth Community Café, a place where parents, staff and community come together to connect.

hotspot.title: Outdoor Nature Play
hotspot.description: The outdoor courtyard and Nature play areas allow families to enjoy a coffee from our Cafe, supervise their children and socialise with others. These spaces are also used by our regular weekly playgroups and parishioners on the weekend.

hotspot.title: Opportunity to Connect
hotspot.description: With its convenient location adjacent to the Catherine Community Centre, our community can come together to enjoy the hospitality and service of the Nazareth Community Café. These community spaces form a central hub where families, staff and community members come together to connect.

hotspot.title: Catherine Community Centre
hotspot.description: The Catherine Community Centre features a large open flexible space utilised for many community programs. Tables and chairs are available to configure the space into both conference style settings as well as information and community forums. Integrated technology supports the many activities the Centre hosts on a weekly basis. The Catherine Community Centre forms an extension of the Our Lady of the Manger Church on a weekly basis.

hotspot.title: Community Programs, Activities and Forums
hotspot.description: The Catherine Community Centre is used to facilitate Community Programs every week. These programs include: Playgroups and FunMoves, a dedicated pre-school program, Wise Owls activities for our senior community members, including Gentle Fitness, Craft, Tai Chai and social events, such as luncheons and presentations as well as family information evenings, conferences and forums.

hotspot.title: Our Lady of the Manger Church
hotspot.description: The Our Lady of the Manger Church is a part of the Hindmarsh/ Findon Parish, where Mass is regularly celebrated. Large folding doors open out the space to cater for larger masses and other religious celebrations such as sacramental celebrations, baptisms and funerals.
